**Author:** Mia Yang | Department of Epidemiology, Rollins School of Public Health, Emory University  
**Partners:** Filling the Nutrition Gap (FNGAP), CARE Nepal, National Farmers Group Federation (NFGF)  
**Live Dashboard:** [Click here to view](https://MiaaaYang.github.io/FNGAP_Data555/)

---

## Why This Project Matters

Poor nutrition, including high rates of anaemia among women and undernutrition among children, remains a critical public health challenge in Nepal, and understanding how women's empowerment and land ownership shape dietary diversity is essential to designing effective interventions. This dashboard enables FNGAP program staff and researchers to interactively explore structural determinants of nutrition across Siraha, Saptari, and Udaypur, supporting evidence-based decisions to improve food security for beneficiary families.

---

## Research Topic

This dashboard examines associations between **women's empowerment**, **household land ownership**, and **dietary diversity** among FNGAP beneficiary families in Nepal. Using cross-sectional survey data from 516 women across three districts in Madhesh Province, the project applies logistic regression and interactive visualizations to explore how structural household resources relate to plant-based and animal-sourced food consumption. Findings are intended to guide FNGAP program planning and future evaluations.

